          "Image": "https://www.dropbox.com/s/l3d2qrn0p6ql8t0/rescue-diver.jpg?raw=1",
          "Title": "RESCUE DIVER",
          "Description": "Learn to save a life",
          "Content": "<h2 style=\"font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: 6px; text-align: center;\">rescue diver COURSE</h2><p style=\"font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: 6px; text-align: center;\"><br></p><p style=\"font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: 6px; text-align: center;\"><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/YNdo9tcgzpM\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe><br></p><div><br></div><table class=\"table table-bordered\"><tbody><tr><td>Being more confident in the water is what every diver desires and the PADI Rescue Diver course will help you get there. It also teaches you to be a better buddy. During the course, you learn how to spot potential problems and quickly deal with them before they become big issues. You'll be ready to rescue someone in an emergency, but you'll also have the skills and awareness to prevent problems. For many, earning a Rescue Diver certification is the start of a career in diving.<br></td></tr></tbody></table><div><br></div><div style=\"text-align: center; \">To sign up for PADI elearning <b>Rescue Diver Course</b> please click on the banner below<br></div><div><br></div><div style=\"text-align: center; \"><a href=\"http://www.padi.com/elearning-scuba-registration/default.aspx?irra=36284&amp;CourseType=resc\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"img-thumbnail\" style=\"width: 650px;\" src=\"https://www.dropbox.com/s/qqu76m8ryppn0hx/Open%20Water%20Static%20Banner%208.jpg?raw=1\"></a><br></div>",
          "vLink": "#/courses/3"
